{
  "stem": "19895.7",
  "chunk_idx": 7,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 244.3,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Because it was very painful to me, that I made it.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "It's guilt feeling.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And I'm sure I'm not the only one who delivered news like this on return.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And then as time went by, and one is jumping back and forth what was life like, it came to news that some people still survived the next death march, and then put it into wagons.",
      "word_count": 36
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "When the-- when the-- when the people who were evacuated from Harka and the other locations which were nearby, as I found out, [NON-ENGLISH], [NON-ENGLISH], [NON-ENGLISH], and many others in that neighborhood, they were all then herded away and taken to [NON-ENGLISH] and Mauthausen, places where very few survived.",
      "word_count": 49
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And many of those names or a couple of those names whom I mentioned, this Edelstein, he had a very Hebrew first name.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "They called him Edelstein, Alter Leiben.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "It was a Yiddish German name.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And Lobo, the name, I never-- maybe they survived, but I never found out in the city of Budapest if they did.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And then [NON-ENGLISH] and Mauthausen, were later on to be found.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "They're very infamous camps where the massacre of thousands and thousands did occur.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So that leads to tell that we still didn't have my mother.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "My grandmother survived in the Ghetto.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "My father survived in the Ghetto, Budapest Ghetto.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Ghetto is not an establishment in Hungary which was there before the Nazi times.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Some towns, and you hear stories about life in middle ages where Jews lived in ghettos.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "But that ghetto was created in the central part of the city, which was heavily Jewishly populated, a certain area where some 80,000, 90,000 Jews were concentrated.",
      "word_count": 27
    }
  ],
